				noOfSun = noOfSun + 1
			elif value.getValueAt(i,'dayNumber') == 2:

			elif value.getValueAt(i,'dayNumber') == 6:
				friTotal = friTotal + value.getValueAt(i,'projection')

			elif value.getValueAt(i,'dayNumber') == 7:
				satTotal = satTotal + value.getValueAt(i,'projection') 
				noOfSat = noOfSat + 1
		## assign teh values
		dailySumDict['Mon'] = monTotal

weeklySumDict = {'Week1':0,'Week1Days':0,'Week2':0,'Week2Days':0,'Week3':0,'Week3Days':0,'Week4':0,'Week4Days':0,'Week5':0,'Week5Days':0}
	if value is not None and value.getRowCount() > 0:
		currentWeek = int(value.getValueAt(0,'weekNumber'))
		weekNo = 1
		weekSum = 0	
		weekName = 'Week'+str(weekNo)
		noOfDaysInWeek = 0
		for i in range(value.getRowCount()):
			
			if int(value.getValueAt(i,'weekNumber')) == currentWeek:
				weekSum = weekSum + value.getValueAt(i,'projection') 
				noOfDaysInWeek = noOfDaysInWeek + 1
			else:
				weeklySumDict[weekName] = weekSum ## add prev week's data 
				weeklySumDict[weekName+'Days'] =noOfDaysInWeek
					
				currentWeek = int(value.getValueAt(i,'weekNumber'))
				weekNo = weekNo + 1
				weekName = 'Week'+str(weekNo)
				weekSum = value.getValueAt(i,'projection') 
				noOfDaysInWeek = 1
		weeklySumDict[weekName] = weekSum
		weeklySumDict[weekName+'Days'] =noOfDaysInWeek	
	return weeklySumDict
